2. cs.GR (Graphics) is also likely as the paper deals with creating a 3D mesh representation of a human body, which is a common problem in computer graphics.
3. cs.MM (Multimedia) is another likely category as the paper deals with processing images and producing a 3D mesh representation of a human body, which is a common problem in multimedia applications.
4. cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also likely as the paper uses an adversarial network to improve the quality of the 3D mesh representation, which is a common technique in machine learning.
5. cs.RO (Robotics) is less likely but still possible as the paper deals with estimating the 3D pose and shape parameters of a human body, which could be useful in robotics applications.
